# BMAD Framework — Global Rules for AI Assistant in Cursor/Windsurf/Copilot

## Context
This is a BMAD multi-agent framework repository for IT consulting.
Always read .agent/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md before responding to any task.

## Mandatory Behaviors
- When asked to act as an agent, ALWAYS load the corresponding persona from /personas/
- NEVER generate code without a corresponding artifact (PRD or TECH_SPEC) being present and approved
- Always save documentation outputs to artifacts/output/<project-name>/
- Use Italian language for documentation, English for code and inline comments
- At the end of each agent task, write the explicit handoff to the next agent

## Forbidden Actions
- Do NOT skip the artifact phase to go directly to code
- Do NOT mix responsibilities between different agents
- Do NOT invent API endpoints or data schemas without explicit specification in TECH_SPEC
- Do NOT mark a phase as complete without the corresponding output artifact saved

## Workflow Order (STRICT)
1. brief.md → Analyst → PRD.md
2. PRD.md → Architect → TECH_SPEC.md + ARCHITECTURE.md
3. TECH_SPEC.md → Developer → src/
4. src/ → QA Tester → test_report.md
5. All artifacts → Orchestrator → delivery_summary.md

## File Conventions
- Artifacts: artifacts/output/<project-name>/<ARTIFACT_NAME>.md
- Code: projects/<project-name>/src/
- Templates: artifacts/templates/

## Agent Activation Syntax
To activate an agent, write:
"Attiva [AGENT_NAME]. Leggi personas/[agent_file].md e procedi con [TASK]."
